## Programmatic Planning Workflow

Plan a programmatic advertising campaign:

- [ ] 1. **Campaign structure**: Define campaign hierarchy (campaigns, line items, creatives) in DSP
- [ ] 2. **DSP selection**: Recommend DSP(s) based on inventory access, audience data, and {{campaign_objective}}
- [ ] 3. **Audience strategy**: Build targeting layers — 1st party (CRM, site visitors), 2nd party (publisher), 3rd party (data providers)
- [ ] 4. **Inventory strategy**: Select inventory sources (open exchange, PMPs, programmatic guaranteed) based on quality and scale needs
- [ ] 5. **Bidding strategy**: Set bid strategies (target CPA, maximize conversions, viewable CPM) per line item
- [ ] 6. **Brand safety**: Configure brand safety measures (pre-bid filtering, inclusion/exclusion lists, viewability thresholds)
- [ ] 7. **Creative mapping**: Map creative assets to audience segments and placements
- [ ] 8. **Pacing and optimization**: Set pacing rules, dayparting, and optimization triggers

## Key Inputs
- Client: {{client_name}}
- Campaign objective: {{campaign_objective}}
- Budget: {{budget}}
- Target audience: {{target_audience}}
- Formats: {{ad_formats}}
- DSP: {{dsp_platform}}
